thub.com/users/bpoldrack/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2021-03-15T12:59:24Z", "updated_at": "2021-05-17T11:52:42Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In the concrete case, someone used `name-storage`, when originally `name` was used, which implied setting up a `name-storage` storage sibling. On the subsequent `create-sibling-ria`, the new sibling `name-storage` now shadows the previous annex special remote, leading to messages like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n% git annex enableremote name-storage url=ria+file:///tmp/mike\r\ngit-annex: That is a normal git remote; passing these parameters does not make sense: url=ria+file:///tmp/mike\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this concrete case the original special remote `name-storage` was not enabled at the time of the second `create-sibling-ria` invocation.\r\n\r\nWe need to prevent this type of conflict.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5499/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5499/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}